"Four camera verbs. Twelve recipes. Every arcade camera you'll want.

The verbs:
- `world/camera-follow! target lag dead-w dead-h` — smooth follow
- `world/camera-snap! x y` — instant reposition
- `world/camera-bounds! x y w h` — clamp to rectangle
- `world/camera-shake! magnitude decay` — screen shake
- `world/camera-pan-to x y` — scripted move
- `world/camera` — read current position

## Follow presets

### Twitchy — reflex shooter

```scheme
(world/camera-follow! player 0.5 20 20)
```

Lag factor 0.5 (half-way each frame — fast catch-up). Small deadzone
(20×20) — camera moves almost as soon as player does. Feels precise.

### Smooth — sidescroller

```scheme
(world/camera-follow! player 0.1 60 40)
```

Lag 0.1 (10% each frame — smooth) with a wider deadzone. Player can
strafe within the deadzone without moving the world.

### Cinematic — story game

```scheme
(world/camera-follow! player 0.03 100 60)
```

Very slow lag (3% each frame — 30+ frames to catch up). Huge deadzone.
Player controls a character in a mostly-static frame. Camera moves
only when they leave the pocket.

## Snap presets

### Boss-fight opener

```scheme
(world/camera-snap! boss-x boss-y)
;; Then wait 30 frames, then transition.
(world/after 30 'begin-fight #f)
```

Cinematically snap to the boss to establish presence, hold, then
resume normal follow.

### Two-player midpoint

```scheme
;; Every frame:
(world/camera-snap! (/ (+ (entity/x p1) (entity/x p2)) 2)
                    (/ (+ (entity/y p1) (entity/y p2)) 2))
```

Instant midpoint camera. Combines with dynamic bounds for a
Bounce-tracking effect.

## Bounds presets

### Sidescroller left-lock

```scheme
(world/camera-bounds! 0 0 (* level-tiles 32) 240)
```

Camera can't scroll left of x=0 or right of level width. Standard.

### Vertical shooter

```scheme
(world/camera-bounds! 0 0 320 (* level-height 32))
```

Only vertical scrolling.

### Boss arena — no exit

```scheme
;; When boss fight starts, lock camera to arena rect.
(world/camera-bounds! arena-x arena-y arena-w arena-h)
```

Player can't walk out of frame. Classic boss-arena feel.

## Shake presets

### Light hit

```scheme
(world/camera-shake! 2 0.85)
```

Two-pixel max shake, 85% decay per frame — fades in 3-4 frames.
Barely felt; used for coin pickups.

### Medium hit

```scheme
(world/camera-shake! 5 0.9)
```

Five-pixel, 90% decay. Used for enemy hit, ordinary boss hit.

### Heavy impact

```scheme
(world/camera-shake! 15 0.95)
```

Big shake, slow decay — 12-15 frames. Used for boss phase transition,
big explosion, screen bomb.

### Sustained rumble

```scheme
(world/camera-shake! 3 0.98)
```

Small magnitude, very slow decay — 30+ frames of subtle shake. Used
for approaching monster, engine rumble, earthquake ambient.

## Pan presets

### Cutscene reveal

```scheme
(world/camera-pan-to treasure-x treasure-y)
;; With additional frames-to-target if runtime supports it.
```

Camera smoothly interpolates from current to target over some number
of frames. Great for revealing a new area or event.

### Follow arrow

```scheme
;; Show player where to go by panning to it.
(world/camera-pan-to goal-x goal-y)
(world/after 60 'return-to-player #f)
```

Then return-to-player handler snaps back.

## Common desktop tasks

**Shop item spotlight.** When a customer clicks a product, briefly
pan to zoom on it with `world/camera-pan-to`. Return to grid after 3
seconds. Physics of attention.

**Notification lens.** For a new message alert, `world/camera-shake!
3 0.98` — very subtle. Enough to draw eye without disrupting.

## Camera troubleshooting

**Camera jitters at high player velocity.** Lag too high combined
with fast movement. Increase deadzone or decrease follow rate.

**Camera stops at level edge but player continues.** By design.
Bounds are limiting camera, not player. Player CAN leave the visible
area — decide if that's fine (some games) or add player bounds too.

**Two-player camera excludes P2.** Midpoint camera loses focus if
players spread. Add dynamic bounds that expand with player distance
(see chapter 15).

**Shake never stops.** Shake decay < 1.0 will always terminate.
Check that decay isn't set to 1.0 or higher.

## The debug-camera-print helper

```scheme
(define (paint-camera-info)
  (let ((cam (world/camera)))
    (paint-text (string-append \"cam: \"
                               (number->string (car cam))
                               \", \"
                               (number->string (cadr cam)))
                10 220)))
```

Add to any on-frame while debugging camera behavior. Shows exact
world position each frame. Confirm camera IS where you think.

## Camera as narrative device

Chapters 6 and 12 use camera-shake for FEEL. Chapter 8's tile world
uses camera-follow + bounds for exploration. Chapter 14's cabinet
uses camera-shake on phase transitions for weight. Chapter 15's
two-player uses snap for midpoint.

In every case, the camera is not just showing the game — it is
TELLING the player what to feel. A shake on impact says 'that hit
mattered.' A pan says 'look here.' A lag says 'take a breath.'

Compose your camera as carefully as you compose your physics.")
